Angola is set to build the first administrative and municipal infrastructure in the coming 18 months in Luongo satellite city, the State Secretary for the Local Authorities, Márcio Daniel has announced. The corner stone for the project has already been launched in the municipality of Catumbela. Also Read: Construction of D.K. Jawara Resort in Barra, Gambia progresses swiftly The US $7m project is under the Integrated Programme for Intervention in Municipalities (PIIM), and will be located in Luongo satellite city. A consortium of three contractors, including Belo Empreendimentos, Soares da Costa and Nov Engenharia e Construções will carry out the project. 